#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Tigase_Server_Extras.rst:5
msgid "3.1. Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Tigase_Server_Extras.rst:7
msgid ""
"Tigase mDNS component provides you with ability to publish domain name of"
" your XMPP server (ending with ``.local``) in the local network using "
"multicast DNS (also known as DNS-SD, Zeroconf or Bonjour)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Tigase_Server_Extras.rst:11
msgid "3.2. Enabling mDNS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Tigase_Server_Extras.rst:13
msgid ""
"To enable this component you need to add mDNS component to your "
"configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Tigase_Server_Extras.rst:20
msgid ""
"This lines will enable mDNS support and will start broadcasting hostname "
"of your host in the local network as ``hostname.local`` and will "
"broadcast DNS records for XMPP server hosted at this domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Tigase_Server_Extras.rst:23
msgid "3.3. Using different domain name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Tigase_Server_Extras.rst:25
msgid ""
"If you are hosting different domain than hostname of your server with "
"``.local`` suffix, then you can set it in mDNS component settings by "
"setting ``serverHost`` property to the name of your domain without suffix"
" ``.local``."
msgstr ""

